THERMAL RESOLVED AND UNRESOLVED ENERGY REGIONS                    2837 1451
 S. F. MUGHABGHAB (BNL) AND A. TRKOV (JSI)                        2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
  This is an updated resonance evaluation for neutron energies    2837 1451
  below 1.0 MeV.                                                  2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
    The thermal capture, scattering cross sections and resonance  2837 1451
  parameters up to 600 keV recommended by Mughabghab [Mu06] are   2837 1451
  adopted in the present evaluation.                              2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
  In addition, the recent LANL capture measurements [Al08]        2837 1451
  showed that the capture width of the 4.5 keV resonance,         2837 1451
  0.76 eV, adopted in the previous evaluation and recommended in  2837 1451
  the Atlas [Mu06] is underestimated. On the other hand, the      2837 1451
  recommended thermal capture cross section  and coherent         2837 1451
  scattering length showed that a bound level is not required to  2837 1451
  describe these data. On this basis, a  capture width of         2837 1451
  2.6008 eV is derived for this resonance from this information.  2837 1451
  With the exception of two the resonances at 42.87 and           2837 1451
  56.91 kev, below 94 keV the scattering widths of other p-wave   2837 1451
  resonances are not known; only capture kernels are recommended  2837 1451
  in the Atlas. For this ENDF evaluation, an average p-wave       2837 1451
  capture width of 0.46 eV {Mu06] and an associated spin value    2837 1451
  are assumed in order to derive scattering widths for these      2837 1451
  resonances from the capture kernels. On the basis of these      2837 1451
  parameters, a Maxwellian capture cross section at a temperature 2837 1451
  of 30 keV is calculated as 24.16 mb compared to directly        2837 1451
  measured values of 23.4-+4.6 mb [D009] and 25.9-+2.6 mb [Na05], 2837 1451
  and a value 25.8-+2.6 derived from the measured poitwise        2837 1451
  capture cross sections. When the capture kernels are incsreased 2837 1451
  by their uncertainties, then the present calculated Maxweliian  2837 1451
  capture cross section becomes 23.8 mb, which is in excellent    2837 1451
  agreement with the three measurments.                           2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
  The energy region from 600 keV to 1 MeV is represented by       2837 1451
  unresolved parameters, which are generated from s- p- and       2837 1451
  d-wave strength functions, in the usual units of 3.20, 0.47 and 2837 1451
  3.20, respectively, and an average s-wave level spacing of      2837 1451
  16.4 keV. The scattering radius in this energy region had to be 2837 1451
  dcreased by about 12% from its value at thermal energy in order 2837 1451
  to follow the experimental data.                                2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
  With these parameters the calculated thermal cross section at   2837 1451
  300 K and resonamce integrals (0.5 eV - 0.1 MeV) are:           2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
           cross section(b)  resonance integral(b)                2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
  total       24.63           456.8                               2837 1451
  elastic      9.72           449.5                               2837 1451
  capture     14.90            7.26                               2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
       The capture Wescott factor=1.00394                         2837 1451
