   This work employed the Hauser-Feshbach code TNG [1,2,3].       2837 1451
 The TNG code provides energy and angular distributions of        2837 1451
 particles emitted in the compound and pre-compound reactions,    2837 1451
 ensures consistency among all reactions, and maintains energy    2837 1451
 balance. Details pertinent to the contents of this evaluation    2837 1451
 can be found in Hetrick et al. [4].                              2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
 DESCRIPTION OF FILES                                             2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
 File 1: GENERAL INFORMATION ------------------------------------ 2837 1451
   MT=451 General information, references, and definitions.       2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
 File 2 RESONANCE PARAMETERS ------------------------------------ 2837 1451
   MT=151 Resonance Parameters; taken from the compilation        2837 1451
     of Mughabghab [5].  From 1.E-5 eV to 600 keV the scattering  2837 1451
     cross section is given completely by the resonance           2837 1451
     parameters.  For total and capture, a contribution is added  2837 1451
     from 10-600 keV due to the capture cross section (see File 3,2837 1451
     MT=102 below).  No background files are given.               2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
     Thermal cross sections values (barns):                       2837 1451
         Total                      24.3                          2837 1451
         Elastic scattering          9.89                         2837 1451
         Capture                    14.4                          2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
        Note that the flag has been set to allow user calculation 2837 1451
     of the angular distributions from the R-Matrix resonance     2837 1451
     parameters, if the user wants angular distributions on a     2837 1451
     finer energy grid than given in File 4, MT=2.                2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
 File 3 CROSS SECTIONS ------------------------------------------ 2837 1451
   MT=1  Total cross section - 1.E-5 eV to 600 keV, given by      2837 1451
     resonance parameters and a contribution from 10 to 600 keV   2837 1451
     which supplements the resonance capture.  From 600 keV to    2837 1451
     20 MeV, natural Ni data of Larson et al. [6] were used as    2837 1451
     no 62Ni data were available.                                 2837 1451
   MT=2  Elastic scattering cross sections were obtained by       2837 1451
     subtracting the nonelastic from the total.                   2837 1451
   MT=3  Nonelastic cross section; sum of MT=4,16,22,28,102-104,  2837 1451
     and 107.                                                     2837 1451
   MT=4  Total inelastic cross section; sum of MT=51-54 and 91.   2837 1451
   MT=16 (n,2n) cross sections were calculated by the TNG code    2837 1451
     [1,2,3,4].  No data available.                               2837 1451
   MT=22 (n,na) cross sections were calculated by the TNG code    2837 1451
     [1,2,3,4].  No data available other than alpha emission.     2837 1451
   MT=28  (n,np)+(n,pn) cross sections were calculated by the TNG 2837 1451
     code [1,2,3,4].  Available data disagree, but data of Qaim   2837 1451
     [7] for (n,np)+(n,pn) includes (n,d). Thus, ENDF/B-V natural 2837 1451
     Ni (n,d) data [8] was normalized so that the TNG calculated  2837 1451
     for (n,np)+(n,pn), + the (n,d) value, fit the Qaim data for  2837 1451
     (n,np)+(n,pn)+(n,d).                                         2837 1451
   MT=51-54 Inelastic scattering exciting levels; results are     2837 1451
     from TNG [1,2,3,4].                                          2837 1451
   MT=91  Inelastic scattering exciting the continuum (TNG        2837 1451
     calculated).                                                 2837 1451
   MT=102 (n,gamma) capture cross section given by resonance      2837 1451
     parameters from 1.E-5 eV to 10 keV.  While the resonance     2837 1451
     parameters contribute up to 600 keV, an additional           2837 1451
     contribution from TNG is included from 10 to 600 keV, due to 2837 1451
     incomplete experimental capture resonance information. The   2837 1451
     same normalization (0.4) used for 58,60Ni was assumed for    2837 1451
     62Ni; the normalized TNG calculations were used from 600 keV 2837 1451
     to 20 MeV.                                                   2837 1451
   MT=103 (n,p) cross sections were calculated by the TNG code    2837 1451
     [1,2,3,4].                                                   2837 1451
   MT=104 (n,d) cross sections were taken from the ENDF/B-V file  2837 1451
     [8] for natural Ni but normalized to be smaller by a factor  2837 1451
     of 5.5 so that the (n,np)+(n,pn)+(n,d) cross section matched 2837 1451
     the data of Qaim [7].                                        2837 1451
   MT=107 (n,a) cross sections were taken from the ENDF/B-V       2837 1451
     activation file but normalized to be smaller by a factor of  2837 1451
     1.9 so that the cross sections fit the available data of     2837 1451
     Qaim et al. [9] and Kneff et al [10].                        2837 1451
                                                                  2837 1451
